milestones.description: Paul Sheahan and Greg Chappell's 103-run partnership is the highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 41 between Ian Redpath and Ian Chappell
Alan Knott and Tony Greig's 77-run partnership is the highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 35 between Rod Marsh and Ross Edwards
Alan Knott and Bob Woolmer's 19-run partnership is the highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 17 between Mallett and Ross Edwards
John Snow and Geoff Arnold's 18-run partnership is the highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Alan Knott and Peter Lever
Bob Woolmer has become the top wicket-taker for ENG in ODIs with 4 wickets, going past Ray Illingworth's 3
Mallett has become the top wicket-taker for AUS in ODIs with 5 wickets, going past Stackpole's 3
This is the highest match aggregate (476) involving teams England & Australia in ODIs
David Colley has conceded the most runs in an innings (72) in ODIs for AUS, going past Alan Connolly's record of 62
Mallett has become the highest wicket-taker in ODIs with 5 wickets, going past Bob Woolmer's 3
Brian Close has broken the record for most ODIs (2) as captain for ENG, going past Ray Illingworth
Ian Chappell has broken the record for most ODIs (2) as captain for AUS, going past Bill Lawry
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for ENG, going past D'Oliveira
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
David Colley has conceded the most runs in an innings (72) in ODIs, going past Alan Connolly's record of 62
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3), going past Greg Chappell
Australia's 240 is the highest total in ODIs, surpassing England's 226
England have broken the record for most extras conceded in an innings 36 in ODIs, going past Australia's 10
Paul Sheahan and Greg Chappell's 103-run partnership is AUS's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between Doug Walters and Ian Chappell
Alan Knott and Tony Greig's 77-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between John Edrich and Alan Knott
Alan Knott and Bob Woolmer's 19-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 15 between John Snow and Alan Knott
John Snow and Geoff Arnold's 18-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Alan Knott and Peter Lever
Stackpole and Ross Edwards's 44-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 19 between Bill Lawry and Stackpole
Ian Chappell and Stackpole's 68-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 62 between Ian Chappell and Stackpole
Paul Sheahan and Greg Chappell's 103-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 41 between Ian Redpath and Ian Chappell
